SIMPLE: presence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presence
<hw>Pres"ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sence</ets>, L. <ets>praesentia</ets>. See
<er>Present</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being present, or
of being within sight or call, or at hand; -- opposed to
<xex>absence</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The place in which one is present; the part of space
within one's ken, call, influence, etc.; neighborhood without the
intervention of anything that forbids intercourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wrath shell be no more⟦br⟧
Thenceforth, but in thy <qex>presence</qex> joy entire.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Specifically, neighborhood to the person of one of
superior of exalted rank; also, presence chamber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In such a <qex>presence</qex> here to plead my thoughts.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An't please your grace, the two great cardinals.⟦br⟧
Wait in the <qex>presence</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The whole of the personal qualities of an
individual; person; personality; especially, the person of a superior,
as a sovereign.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Sovran <qex>Presence</qex> thus replied.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>An assembly, especially of person of rank or
nobility; noble company.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Odmar, of all this <qex>presence</qex> does contain,⟦br⟧
Give her your wreath whom you esteem most fair.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Port, mien; air; personal appearence.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Rather dignity of presence than beauty of aspect.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A graceful <qex>presence</qex> bespeaks acceptance.</q> <rj><qau>
Collier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Presence chamber</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Presence room</b></col></mcol>, <cd>the room in which a great
personage receives company.</cd> <au>Addison.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Chambers
of presence</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Bacon.</au> -- <col><b>Presence of
mind</b></col>, <cd>that state of the mind in which all its faculties
are alert, prompt, and acting harmoniously in obedience to the will,
enabling one to reach, as it were spontaneously or by intuition, just
conclusions in sudden emergencies.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presensation</ent>⟦br⟧
